    "Driving under the influence of alcohol delays reaction times and impairs judgment, significantly increasing the likelihood of a crash (21, 22, 29).",
    "Second, the crash occurred during road maintenance operation, which further increased the risk of the crash.",
    "Road maintenance can narrow or create irregularities in the roadway, making driving conditions more challenging (59, 60).",
    "Third, the dark lighting conditions and wet road surface limited the driver's visibility and increased stopping distances, thereby heightening the risk of a crash (28, 29).",
    "Fourth, the high speed of the roadway segment at the time of the crash also contributed to the severity of the crash."
